On Sunday morning, the convoy of Borno’s Gov Babagana Zulu was attacked around Baga where he went to resettle some IDPs.
Although no death was recorded in the Sunday attack on while Zulum was on his way back to Maiduguri, some soldiers were wounded.
According to report, the windscreens of some vehicle were scattered; some vehicles had their tyres burst by gunshots, including the Government House Press Crew bus.
The military gun truck came under fire, and a soldier had his shoulder scalded with gunshot.
The governor had on Sunday resettled 521 households displaced from Baga, and he went to Monguno to address the IDPs there.
